# Next.js Production Standards

Every production app lives under `Frontend_Nextjs/NN-site-name/` and is migrated from an approved HTML file in `sites/`.

## Tech contract

- **Next.js 15** App Router, **React 19**, **TypeScript**, **Tailwind CSS v4**
- Dark mode via `next-themes` with CSS custom properties mirroring HTML token names
- No inline copy blocks, nav arrays, or brand constants in TSX — use `config/` and `content/`
- Content accessed through repository interfaces in `lib/content/` (local JSON now, CMS/API later)

## Mandatory folder anatomy

```
Frontend_Nextjs/NN-site-name/
  app/                    # App Router pages + layouts
  components/
    ui/                   # Button, Card, Badge, FormField, Container
    layout/               # Header, Footer, MobileNav, ThemeToggle
    sections/             # Homepage sections
    views/                # Full-page view components
    seo/                  # JsonLd, metadata helpers
  config/site.config.ts   # Brand, locale, SEO defaults, env-driven domain
  content/                # JSON (+ optional MDX for long prose)
  lib/content/            # types, repositories, providers
  hooks/                  # Client behavior ported from initX()
  public/                 # Static assets
```

## No-hardcoding rules (blocking)

- Brand name, phone, domain → `config/site.config.ts` or env (`NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL`)
- Navigation, footer links → `content/navigation.json` via repository
- Page copy, FAQ, testimonials, products → typed `content/` files
- Colors, spacing, radius, shadows → Tailwind theme tokens + CSS vars (same names as HTML `--color-*`, `--space-*`)
- Data fetching → repository layer, never embedded in UI components

## Component conventions

- Server Components by default; `'use client'` only for interactivity (nav drawer, forms, theme toggle, calculators)
- BEM class names from HTML may map to Tailwind utilities but preserve semantic component boundaries
- One hook per former `initX()` function; compose in client wrappers
- Props typed with interfaces from `lib/content/types.ts`

## Quality targets

- Lighthouse: Performance 95+, Accessibility 100, SEO 100, Best Practices 100
- WCAG 2.2 AA+; keyboard navigation; `prefers-reduced-motion` respected
- `pnpm build` passes with zero TypeScript errors
- Visual parity with source HTML at 320px–2560px in both themes

## Parity enforcement (blocking before sign-off)

- **Interactive routes** (quote, calculator, contact, rebates, inspection) MUST be React views — never prose JSON with embedded `<form>` HTML
- **No emoji** as icon substitutes in production components — use `components/icons/`
- **Component CSS port** required in `@layer components` before Phase 9 sign-off
- **Sticky CTA** mobile-only (`lg:hidden`); bottom nav with SVG icons + scroll-hide
- **FAB**, toast, and lead-save hooks required when present in source HTML

